  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Decision is Not accepted because the achieved credibility level for Test conditions (Gradation 1) falls below the required level (Gradation 2), and the E/uval ratio marginally exceeds the pre-established 1.96 threshold for two of three QoIs, preventing a finding of sufficient model credibility for regulatory submission.",
